        "title": "5. `models.py`",
        "content": "Low-value but cheap — mostly a sanity check that defaults behave (particularly `images: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)`, since a plain mutable default would be a classic bug).\n\n```python\nfrom models import Article, SiteSelectors\n\nclass TestModels:\n    def test_article_images_default_is_independent_list(self):\n        a1 = Article(url=\"u\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                      category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n        a2 = Article(url=\"u2\", title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                      category=None, source=\"s\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n        a1.images.append(\"http://x\")\n        assert a2.images == []  # would fail if default_factory were a shared mutable default\n\n    def test_site_selectors_optional_defaults(self):\n        s = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\")\n        assert s.author is None\n        assert s.published_date_attr is None\n        assert s.published_date_format is None\n        assert s.category is None\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
